<subSubSection id="44911484C518BD59FF15FDC95201FCCE" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="0C34470FC518BD59FF15FDC952B8FCE2" blockId="8.[151,1437,613,1000]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC518BD59FF15FDC9507EFDCA" bold="true" box="[151,278,613,639]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Type data:</emphasis>
Friese proposed this species based on an undetermined number of male and female specimens collected by the German explorer, insect trader and entomologist Hans Fruhstorfer (1866–1922) in the Brazilian states of Amazonas and 
<collectingRegion id="CE4F89EDC518BD59FEC7FD015088FD72" box="[325,480,685,711]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
. A single male collected in this latter state was found at 
<collectionCode id="6A9ADFCAC518BD59FBD9FD0255F2FD7D" box="[1115,1178,686,712]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
, being here designated the 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC518BD59FF40FD7D5044FD5E" box="[194,300,721,747]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: [green label with black rim] Minas Geraës 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC518BD59FA9BFD7D5434FD5E" box="[1305,1372,721,747]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Brasil</collectingCountry>
1897 ex. coll. Fruhstorfer [printed]\ Coll. Friese [printed]\ [red label] Typus [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC518BD59FB9DFD5A546BFCA5" authority="Fr" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[1055,1283,757,784]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviceps">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC518BD59FB9DFD5A558BFCBA" box="[1055,1251,757,784]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Centris breviceps</emphasis>
Fr
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount id="1A8D8C86C518BD59FA88FD5A5477FCA5" box="[1290,1311,758,784]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
[handwrit-ten 1909 Friese det. [printed]\ [light blue label] 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC518BD59FD32FCB55238FC86" box="[688,848,793,819]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC518BD59FCD5FCB655C5FC86" authority="Friese, 1899" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[855,1197,793,820]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviceps">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC518BD59FCD5FCB65573FC86" box="[855,1051,793,820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Centris breviceps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC518BD59FBA1FCB555C5FC86" author="Friese, H." box="[1059,1197,793,819]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref21677" refString="Friese, H. (1899) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
des. F. Vivallo, 2017 [printed] (
<collectionCode id="6A9ADFCAC518BD59FE8AFC915022FCE2" box="[264,330,829,855]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
). The current condition of the 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC518BD59FD1CFC915228FCE2" box="[670,832,829,855]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C34470FC518BD59FF45FCCD5201FCCE" blockId="8.[151,1437,613,1000]" box="[199,873,865,892]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<materialsCitation id="BCE34D52C518BD59FF45FCCD520CFCCE" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3014903401" box="[199,868,865,892]" country="Brazil" location="Minas Gerais state" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Minas Gerais" typeStatus="holotype">
